        <h5>Lake Minchumina</h5>
        <h6>April 5 </h6>
        <q>Trapping trail through burned forest. The 2015 Carlson Lake Burn had a few places where deadfall seriously impeded travel the first time through, requiring prodigious use of chain saw. This delayed getting the trail opened up during a critical time. It also required a halfway tent camp to be used; normally we donâ€™t have to camp out for this run.</q>
        <p>This change affects trapping and occurs every few years. This change has a strong effect on safety.</p>
